This article provides a fact sheet on the actions taken by the United States to address the violence and human rights abuses in Syria. The US has implemented various measures including executive orders, sanctions, and other financial actions. These actions aim to increase pressure on the Syrian regime and support the Syrian people's demand for a democratic transition. Some of the key actions taken include the signing of a new executive order that blocks the property of the Syrian government and bans certain transactions with Syria, the designation of individuals and entities involved in human rights abuses and proliferation activities, and efforts at the United Nations to condemn the Syrian government's actions and push for accountability.